  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and cook until softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, and cayenne pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in doenjang. Cook for 1-2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add broth and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20-25 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
